gomodel:SYNGO_3788  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Immunoreactivity of dystrophin and dystrophin isoforms was widely distributed throughout the ganglionic neurons. About 60-65% of more than 100 observed postsynaptic specializations are immunopositive (Fig. 3A,B). Although our observations were conducted at the surface of the specimens, within the range of antibody penetration, the risk of false negatives is still high, especially for structures as thin as these ganglionic postsynaptic densities, and the above percentage may represent an underestimate. Presynaptic boutons were never labelled (Fig. 3A,B).\". Experimental description: \"Immunolocalization of dystrophin and its isoforms by electron microscopy in normal mouse superior cervical ganglion\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3788" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

